  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "The axolotl half of the duet. Low partial count, slow vibrato at 4 Hz — Oscar's languid warmth rendered as a baritone hum. Effort 0.3 keeps things in gentle mezzo territory where Oscar is most comfortable. Drama at 0.3 means partials barely synchronize, producing a warm, breathy haze rather than a crisp choir. The sound of contentment. Pair with feliX Sings for the full duet.",
